data.name: Grilled Lemon Herb Chicken with Garlic Parmesan Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: Succulent grilled chicken infused with zesty lemon and aromatic herbs, paired with creamy garlic parmesan mashed potatoes for a delightful comfort meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.
In a bowl, mix lemon juice, olive oil, minced garlic, parsley, thyme, salt, and pepper. Add chicken breasts and marinate for at least 15 minutes.
While the chicken is marinating, boil the potatoes in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes.
Once potatoes are cooked, drain and return to the pot. Add butter, milk, grated parmesan, garlic powder, and pepper. Mash until smooth and creamy.
Grill the marinated chicken for about 6-7 minutes on each side or until fully cooked and juices run clear.
Serve the grilled chicken alongside the garlic parmesan mashed potatoes. Enjoy!
